&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Electrical Engineer 2 will support designing, developing, and maintaining electrical systems and components across multiple R&amp;amp;D efforts and production lines. This key player will combine technical expertise and problem-solving skills to design, implement, and maintain a broad range of electrical systems in various domains including embedded systems (simulation, schematic capture, PCB layout, firmware development), power electronics, radio frequency (RF) devices and antennas, battery and associated management systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Functions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop and test electrical systems and equipment for military, industrial, commercial, and consumer use related to Unmanned Systems (UAVs, UGVs, USVs) of various types.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the development and maintenance of electrical system documentation including wiring diagrams and schematics through an organized release process utilizing modern distributed version control technologies such as GIT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the design, test, and review new and existing PCB designs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze and interpret technical data, such as specifications, blueprints, and schematics, to ensure compliance with applicable codes and regulations. Familiarity with military standards related to reliability and safety is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other engineers, technicians, and clients to identify and resolve technical issues and improve system performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the installation, operation, maintenance, and repair of electrical systems and equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot electrical problems and provide technical support to production staff as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement automated programming and testing apparatuses to aid in production and quality assurance of circuit boards and subassemblies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support rapid prototyping, system bring-up, and hardware-in-the-loop (HIL) testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to internal R&amp;amp;D efforts and aid in the transition of these efforts into production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Standard Essential Functions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular and reliable attendance on a full time basis [or in accordance with posted schedule].&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for exhibiting professional behavior with both internal and external business associates that reflects positively on the company and is consistent with the company&#39;s policies and practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embodies AEVEX’s cultural values and aligns daily actions with department goals and company culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
