&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of electrical design software for schematic capture and PCB layout (Altium (Preferred), Eagle PCB, Autodesk Fusion360, KICAD, etc...)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of electrical simulation tools such as LTspice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Radio Frequency (RF) simulation tools such as ANSYS HFSS or CST Microwave Studio is beneficial.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Limited MCAD skills with Autodesk Fusion360 and/or SolidWorks are beneficial.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of common industry protocols (LVDS, I2C, HDMI, UART, SPI, CAN, USB, MIPI)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with battery-powered Unmanned Aerial Vehicles (UAVs) and associated avionics and electronics

