&lt;p&gt;AEVEX is seeking a Global Freight Specialist (Hazardous Materials Certified) responsible for coordinating domestic and international freight shipments, ensuring full compliance with regulatory, customer, and company requirements. This role manages end-to-end logistics activities including carrier coordination, shipment documentation, and export processes for aerospace components and systems. The Specialist is responsible for preparing, reviewing, and signing hazardous goods declarations in accordance with Department of Transportation (DOT) and International Air Transport Association (IATA) regulations. This position ensures all hazardous and non-hazardous shipments are properly classified, packaged, labeled, and documented to meet applicable domestic and international shipping standards. This role works closely with program teams, warehouse operations, and external freight forwarders to ensure timely, compliant, and cost-effective delivery of materials worldwide. The position also supports compliance with AS9100 requirements, including documentation accuracy, traceability, and audit readiness. The Global Freight Specialist (Hazardous Materials Certified) plays a critical role in enabling global operations while minimizing risk and ensuring adherence to all applicable transportation and export regulations.&lt;/p&gt;
